HEADWORD: Leachy
<hw>Leach"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Permitting liquids to
pass by percolation; not capable of retaining water; porous; pervious;
-- said of gravelly or sandy soils, and the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lead</ent>⟦br⟧
